
[1]baptistery

   BAP'TISTERY, n. [L. baptisterium.] A place where the sacrament of
   baptism is administered. Primitively, baptisteries were in buildings
   separate from the church; but in the sixth century, they were taken
   into the church-porch, and afterwards into the church itself.
